shapelib â€” LibreCAD vendoring notes
====================================

Upstream
--------
- Version : 1.6.3
- Source  : https://download.osgeo.org/shapelib/shapelib-1.6.3.tar.gz
- Home    : https://shapelib.maptools.org/
- License : dual MIT / LGPL (see LICENSE-MIT, LICENSE-LGPL)

Purpose in LibreCAD
-------------------
This library backs the native ESRI Shapefile (.shp) import filter
(`RS_FilterSHP`, `librecad/src/lib/filters/rs_filtershp.{h,cpp}`).  It is
imported into LibreCAD as source so we can compile it as C++17 alongside the
rest of the codebase â€” see `docs/plan_shp_native_filter.md` for the plan that
introduced it.

Sources live directly under `src/`.  Layout mirrors upstream so a resync is a
straight `.c â†’ .cpp` overwrite followed by re-applying the (deliberately
small) delta list below.

Build integration
-----------------
- CMake (top `CMakeLists.txt`): sources compile directly into `librecad_lib`
  under `${SHARED_INCLUDES}` â€” mirrors how `libraries/jwwlib/*` is wired.
- qmake6 (`libraries/shapelib/shapelib.pro`): builds a static lib linked into
  the main app via `librecad/src/src.pro` (`PRE_TARGETDEPS`/`-lshapelib`).
  Added in Phase 1b.

Local deltas vs upstream
------------------------
Kept intentionally minimal so upstream CVE-fix resyncs stay cheap:

1. **Filename rename** (Phase 1b): `shpopen.c`, `dbfopen.c`, `safileio.c`
   renamed to `.cpp` and compiled as C++17.  Upstream already emits C++-style
   casts under `__cplusplus` (see `shapefil_private.h` cast macros and the
   `extern "C"` guards in `shapefil.h`), so `shpopen.cpp` compiles cleanly
   with `clang++ -std=c++17 -Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic` without any source
   edits.
2. **`dbfopen.cpp` CPLsprintf dedupe** (Phase 1b): the upstream file defines
   `CPLsprintf`/`CPLsnprintf` twice â€” once before the MSVC snprintf shim
   (upstream lines 25-26) and once after (lines 48-49).  The pre-shim block
   is redundant (sprintf has no shim; snprintf is remapped just below), so
   it was removed.  A comment in-place marks the delta.
3. **`safileio.cpp` old-style casts modernised** (Phase 1b): every C-style
   cast in this file (both the POSIX hooks and the Windows
   `SHPAPI_WINDOWS`/UTF-8 hooks) converted to `reinterpret_cast` for
   pointer-vs-pointer conversions (SAFileâ†”FILE*, mallocâ†’wchar_t*, etc.) and
   `static_cast` for numeric widenings (SAOffsetâ†”size_t/long/__int64,
   strlenâ†’int).  Semantics unchanged; the file now compiles cleanly under
   `-Wold-style-cast`.

Resync procedure
----------------
When picking up a new upstream release (e.g., after a CVE fix):

1. Download the upstream tarball.
2. Overwrite `src/{shpopen,dbfopen,safileio,shapefil,shapefil_private}.*`
   with the upstream files (as `.c` and `.h`).
3. Re-rename the three translation units back to `.cpp`.
4. Re-apply the delta list above (a, b).
5. Update this file's `Version` line and diff.
6. Run the Phase-0 corpus safety net â€”
   `ctest --test-dir build-test -R librecad_tests --output-on-failure` after
   `cmake --build build-test --target librecad_tests -j12` â€” to prove
   behavior is unchanged over the 31 corpus shapefiles under `test_data/shp/`.
7. Also run `qmake6 librecad.pro && make -j12` to confirm the dual build.
